    {
        "content": "<p>Nevermind, I see <code>zero_mul</code>/<code>mul_zero</code>.</p>",
        "id": 217881765,
        "sender_full_name": "Anne Baanen",
        "timestamp": 1606309740
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Looks like it was a consequence of <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/issues/2707\">#2707</a>, moving the algebraic hierarchy from core to mathlib, coming after <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/issues/2242\">#2242</a>, defining <code>group_with_zero</code>.</p>",
        "id": 217882583,
        "sender_full_name": "Anne Baanen",
        "timestamp": 1606310203
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there anyway way to do this type of extension but tell lean that the base class axioms can be inferred from the child class?</p>",
        "id": 217883276,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1606310636
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could use <code>auto_param</code>/<code>opt_param</code>s, see e.g. how <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/lean/blob/ed6accfb611bbd28ef5b7e34361d2b58a366e2c9/library/init/algebra/order.lean#L26\"><code>preorder</code></a> defines <code>(&lt;)</code>.</p>",
        "id": 217883435,
        "sender_full_name": "Anne Baanen",
        "timestamp": 1606310711
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(In fact, the reason I'm asking is that I'm checking what happens if we add a default <code>has_div</code> to <code>group(_with_zero)</code>, e.g. to solve the diamond <code>field -&gt; euclidean_domain -&gt; has_div; field -&gt; group_with_zero -&gt; has_div</code>.)</p>",
        "id": 217883578,
        "sender_full_name": "Anne Baanen",
        "timestamp": 1606310792
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/preorder\">docs#preorder</a></p>",
        "id": 217883611,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1606310810
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it a nontrivial diamond?</p>",
